  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Capacity Building in Disaster Risk Reduction in the United Republic of Tanzania</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of this project is to support the Disaster Risk Reduction (DRR) Strategy of the United Republic of Tanzania through community-based disaster risk management (CBDRM). The project empowers communities and government ministries, departments and agencies in taking appropriate actions and effective measures in DRR and management resulting in the saving of lives, protection of the environment and the economy, and national resilience. The project includes capacity-building activities, such as transborder table top exercises on response to disaster risk; training of trainers on mental health and psychosocial support provision; a mentorship programme to disaster response volunteers in the community while integrating gender, vulnerable groups&#x2019; needs and cultural diversity into DRR; convening the DRR coordination working groups quarterly; and awareness-raising programme on CBDRM to communities at risk in the United Republic of Tanzania.</narrative>
  </description>
